---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "La Cornue Range Repair Los Angeles | Château & CornuFé Specialists";
const description = "Expert La Cornue range repair in Los Angeles. Château, CornuFé, French top, vaulted convection oven — Saint-Ouen since 1908. Serial-specific parts, same-day service. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — La Cornue Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-la-cornue-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "La Cornue Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"La Cornue Château Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"La Cornue CornuFé Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"La Cornue French Top Service"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"La Cornue Vaulted Oven Service"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"La Cornue Grand Palais Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"La Cornue Teppanyaki Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does La Cornue range repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most La Cornue repairs run $225–$780. Common fixes like thermocouple replacement, door gasket, thermostat calibration, or French top cleaning service are on the lower end. Control board, gas valve, or specialty component replacement runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Parts typically run 20-30% higher than domestic brands due to French manufacturing sourcing. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between La Cornue Château and CornuFé?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The Château is La Cornue's fully bespoke range — each one is built to order in Saint-Ouen with customer-specified colors, configurations, and custom elements. Château ranges have virtually unlimited customization and correspondingly longer delivery times and higher prices. The CornuFé is La Cornue's semi-standard range — available in fixed sizes (90cm and 110cm) with a curated color palette, faster availability, and somewhat more accessible pricing. Both use the same fundamental vaulted oven design and French manufacturing quality. Service approach differs: Château serial numbers determine exact part specifications; CornuFé uses standardized part numbers after specific serial thresholds."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is La Cornue's vaulted oven and why is it different to service?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "La Cornue's vaulted (arched) oven ceiling is the brand's original innovation from 1908 — the curved ceiling creates natural convection circulation without a fan, channeling heat around food from all sides. The result is more even cooking than a standard rectangular oven cavity. For service, the vaulted geometry means heat distribution and temperature sensing differ from rectangular ovens. Temperature calibration requires accounting for the dome's thermal behavior, and thermostat probe placement is specific to the vaulted design."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the La Cornue French Top and what are the common failures?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The French Top (also called Piano Top or Plaque) is a solid cast iron cooking plate heated from below — replacing individual open burners in certain La Cornue configurations. It creates graduated heat zones from intense (center, directly over the burner) to gentle (edge, away from the burner). Common failures: the dedicated burner beneath the plate partially blocks, creating non-uniform plate temperatures; the thermocouple for the French top burner degrades; or the cast iron plate develops hot spots from uneven seasoning. We service the French top as a standalone system."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does La Cornue require serial-number-specific parts?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "La Cornue has updated component specifications at specific production milestones — particularly for gaskets, safety valves, and control components. For example, CornuFé 90 gaskets use different part numbers before and after serial number 185000. Château gaskets changed specification in July 2021. Using the wrong serial-era part creates fitting problems that can affect performance and safety. We identify serial numbers before ordering any La Cornue parts to ensure correct specification."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where is La Cornue made?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "La Cornue is made in Saint-Ouen, a commune in the northern suburbs of Paris, France. The company was founded in 1908 by Albert Dupuy, who invented the first convection oven — using a vaulted ceiling to circulate heat around food. Every La Cornue range is handcrafted at the Saint-Ouen workshop, making it one of the most authentically artisan-produced ranges in the world."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .compare-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .compare-card { background: #161616; padding: 24px 22px; }
  .compare-card.featured { border-top: 2px solid var(--red); }
  .compare-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .compare-name { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .compare-desc { font-size: 13px; color: #666; line-height: 1.65; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-history { border-color: #2a5ea5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-history .tip-label { color: #2a5ea5; }
  .tip-serial { border-color: #c8820a; background: #fff8f0; }
  .tip-serial .tip-label { color: #c8820a; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-french-top { background: #c8820a; }
  .tag-vault { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-enamel { background: #5a2a7a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .compare-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">La Cornue Range Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        La Cornue Repair.<br/>
        <span>Château. CornuFé.</span><br/>
        Saint-Ouen, 1908.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        La Cornue invented convection in 1908 with a vaulted oven ceiling. The Château is handbuilt to order; the CornuFé is semi-standard — but both require the same serial-specific parts knowledge, the same French Top diagnostic approach, and the same reverence for what these ranges represent. We bring all of it.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">French Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Serial-Specific Parts Expertise</span>
    <span class="trust-item">French Top / Piano Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Vaulted Oven Calibration</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About La Cornue</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The First Convection Oven. Saint-Ouen, Paris. Since 1908.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      In 1908, in Saint-Ouen on the northern edge of Paris, Albert Dupuy invented the convection oven. Not convection as we use the term today — with a fan — but true natural convection: a vaulted, arched oven ceiling that channeled heat in a continuous circulation around the food, cooking it evenly from all sides without mechanical intervention. While most ovens of the era were flat-topped boxes that heated food from below, Dupuy's vaulted design enveloped food in heat. La Cornue has been refining that insight ever since.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Today La Cornue produces two product families. The Château is La Cornue's fully bespoke range — handbuilt to the customer's exact specification at the Saint-Ouen workshop in virtually any size, color, configuration, and with custom elements found nowhere else. The CornuFé is La Cornue's semi-standard range — available in 90cm and 110cm with a curated color palette and faster availability. Both use the vaulted oven, both are handcrafted in France, and both require service knowledge that extends well beyond generic range repair.
    </p>

    <div class="compare-grid">
      <div class="compare-card featured">
        <div class="compare-label">Fully Bespoke · Handbuilt to Order</div>
        <div class="compare-name">Château</div>
        <div class="compare-desc">Built to the customer's exact specification — custom sizes from 75cm to the Grand Palais 180cm, virtually unlimited color choices, custom burner configurations, French top arrangements, teppanyaki, warming drawers, and elements available in no other range. Each Château is a unique object. Serial numbers determine exact part specifications — parts ordered without serial verification may not fit. Lead times reflect the custom build process.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="compare-card">
        <div class="compare-label">Semi-Standard · Curated Options</div>
        <div class="compare-name">CornuFé</div>
        <div class="compare-desc">La Cornue's more accessible line — 90cm and 110cm configurations in a curated palette of colors and standard trim options. Faster availability than the fully bespoke Château. Still handcrafted in Saint-Ouen, still uses the vaulted oven design. Parts are more standardized but still serial-number-specific at key production milestones (gaskets, safety valves). The most common La Cornue in LA residential kitchens.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-history" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🏛️ The Vaulted Oven — Why It Matters for Service</div>
      <div class="tip-text">La Cornue's arched oven ceiling isn't decorative — it's functional. The dome shape creates a natural circulation pattern: heat from the oven burner or element rises, follows the arch to the top, and flows down the sides to circulate continuously around the food. This produces exceptional even cooking without a convection fan. For service, the vaulted geometry changes temperature measurement and calibration: a thermostat probe placed at the standard height in a rectangular oven will read differently in La Cornue's dome. We calibrate La Cornue oven temperature accounting for the dome's thermal behavior — not using the flat-oven standard that most temperature service is based on.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every La Cornue Configuration We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All La Cornue models — Château, CornuFé, Grand Palais — across all configurations. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Château Range Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">The fully bespoke La Cornue Château — handbuilt to specification, present in LA's most significant residential kitchens. Château service requires knowing the specific serial number before any parts work begins: gasket specifications, safety valve components, and control parts have changed at specific production dates and serial number thresholds. We verify serial numbers as the first step of every Château service call. The Saint-Ouen workshop's bespoke nature also means some Château configurations have components with no direct CornuFé equivalent.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: thermocouple failure · gas valve · oven temperature calibration (dome-specific) · door gasket (serial-specific) · French top service · warming drawer · control knobs · coastal enamel care</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌀</div>
        <div class="service-name">CornuFé Range Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">The La Cornue CornuFé — 90cm and 110cm semi-standard configurations in the curated palette. The most common La Cornue in LA residential kitchens. CornuFé parts are more standardized than Château, but key components (gaskets, safety valves) have different part numbers before and after specific serial number thresholds. CornuFé 90 gaskets use different part numbers before and after serial number 185000; CornuFé 110 at 196000. We confirm serial numbers before ordering any CornuFé gaskets or safety components.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: thermocouple · oven temperature drift · door gasket (serial-specific: before/after S/N 185000 or 196000) · igniter · gas valve · convection fan (if fitted) · control panel · burner blockage</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍳</div>
        <div class="service-name">French Top (Piano) Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">La Cornue's French Top — a solid cast iron cooking plate heated from beneath by a dedicated burner — creates graduated heat zones from searing-hot center to gentle-warm edge. The French top is La Cornue's most distinctive cooking surface and a specific service subsystem. Common failures: the dedicated burner partially blocks (uneven plate temperature), the thermocouple for the French top circuit degrades (plate temperature drops), or the cast iron plate accumulates uneven seasoning from LA's cooking oil environment. We service the French top as an independent system.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: dedicated burner blockage · thermocouple failure · uneven plate temperature · hot spots · seasoning service · igniter · gas circuit</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🥩</div>
        <div class="service-name">Teppanyaki &amp; Specialty Surface Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">La Cornue's teppanyaki surface — an optional configuration on Château and larger CornuFé arrangements — uses a steel cooking plate with dedicated heat control. Teppanyaki thermostat drift and dedicated burner issues are the most common failures. Also: Château warming drawers, rotisserie configurations, and bespoke accessory elements that exist only on custom-ordered Château ranges. We approach each bespoke configuration with the specific knowledge of what La Cornue installed.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: teppanyaki thermostat drift · dedicated burner · temperature inconsistency · warming drawer element · rotisserie motor · custom configuration assessment</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Vaulted Oven Temperature Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">La Cornue's vaulted oven requires calibration specific to the dome geometry. Heat distribution in the arch is different from a rectangular cavity — the natural circulation pattern that makes La Cornue cooking exceptional also means temperature measurement must account for the dome's thermal dynamics. We use a multi-point temperature test across the oven cavity, not a single-point reading, before any thermostat adjustment or sensor replacement on La Cornue oven calls.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: oven running hot or cold · multi-point temperature test · dome-specific calibration · door gasket seal · convection mode fault · thermostat · temperature sensor · door hinge</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">✨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Enamel &amp; Finish Care</div>
        <div class="service-desc">La Cornue's enamel finish — available in the full Château custom palette and a curated CornuFé selection — is vitrified at the Saint-Ouen workshop. Non-abrasive service protocols apply to all La Cornue enamel work. Château ranges with custom-color enamel panels that need replacement require ordering from Saint-Ouen with lead times that reflect the custom production process. We identify enamel color specifications before any service that might require panel replacement.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">All service with enamel-safe cleaning agents and protective covers. Color-spec documentation for any exterior component work. Lead time disclosure before ordering custom enamel panels.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-serial" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🔢 Serial Numbers — Why They're Critical for La Cornue Parts</div>
      <div class="tip-text">La Cornue updated gasket and safety valve specifications at specific serial number thresholds. For CornuFé 90: gaskets use Part No. P033451 before serial 185000, and Part No. P067490 after. For CornuFé 110: the same threshold applies at serial 196000. For Château ranges: gasket specification changed in July 2021 (Part No. 06FPGV01-100 for ranges before July 2021; Part No. 06RM01 for ranges after). Ordering the wrong serial-era gasket creates a seal that doesn't fit the door correctly — and an incorrectly sealed oven door affects both temperature performance and efficiency. We locate the serial number plate (inside the left storage drawer on most models) before ordering any gasket or safety valve for any La Cornue.</div>
    </div>
